{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fdd0df22-099d-4647-88ac-efb99b039b3f","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nThe old VSTest `--filter` syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~X&Category=Y`) doesn't work with MTP. Use the `--filter` flag with MTP's **treenode filter** syntax instead:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n- `/**/*IntegrationTests*` — matches any test whose fully qualified name contains \"IntegrationTests\" (replaces `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests`)\n- `[Category=Smoke]` — matches the trait (replaces `Category=Smoke`)\n\n### 2. Missing MTP test runner package\n\nYour `.csproj` enables MTP (`UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner`) but is missing the required runner package. Add it:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.1\" />\n```\n\n### Updated CI command\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\nThis is the MTP equivalent of your original `--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7f241e55-6ba3-4c46-9355-ce275a1fbedc","outputTokens":306,"requestId":"CFCA:2D9C3A:604C65F:6B8619B:69EC0F6F"},"id":"f5261acb-8d54-4f5f-b84c-bbf4a075b5b7","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:48:57.125Z","parentId":"604ecbc1-5062-4193-86e1-eddf7f2ad9e5"}
